{SECT 0 {EXCHG {PARA 211 "" 0 "" {TEXT 206 26 "Dynamic Equations For \+
The " }}{PARA 212 "" 0 "" {TEXT 206 60 "Second Stage Of The 2-DOF Seri
al Flexible Link (2DSFL) Robot" }}{PARA 209 "" 0 "" {TEXT 206 1 "\251"
 }{TEXT 228 29 " 2008 Quanser Consulting Inc." }}{PARA 19 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 206 5 "URL: " }{HYPERLNK 17 "http://www.quanser.com" 4 "http://w
ww.quanser.com" "" }{TEXT 229 0 "" }}}{PARA 207 "" 0 "Description" 
{TEXT 230 0 "" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" {TEXT 231 11 "Description" }}
{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 167 "This worksheet presents the general dy
namic equations modelling the Second Stage Of Quanser's 2-DOF Serial F
lexible Link (2DSFL) Robot, assuming a decoupled modelling." }}{PARA 
15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 83 "This worksheet derives the state-space matric
es used in the control implementation." }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 
72 "The Lagrange's method is used to obtain the dynamic model of the s
ystem." }}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 4 "The " }{TEXT 207 13 "Qu
anser_Tools" }{TEXT 233 8 " Package" }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 4 "T
he " }{TEXT 208 13 "Quanser_Tools" }{TEXT 232 228 " module defines gen
eric procedures and data in relation to determining the state-space re
presentation of all the Quanser experiments. Specifically, this means \+
deriving and solving the Lagrange's equations of the Quanser systems."
 }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 4 "The " }{TEXT 209 7 "quanser" }{TEXT 
232 27 " repository containing the " }{TEXT 210 13 "Quanser_Tools" }
{TEXT 232 50 " package is implemented in the 2 following files: " }
{TEXT 211 11 "quanser.ind" }{TEXT 232 5 " and " }{TEXT 212 12 "quanser
.lib." }{TEXT 232 110 " If these two files are not readily available, \+
they can be generated by executing the Maple worksheet titled: " }
{TEXT 213 17 "quanser_tools.mws" }{TEXT 232 1 "." }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 214 10 "To install" }{TEXT 232 5 " the " }{TEXT 215 13 "Quanser_
Tools" }{TEXT 232 29 " package, copy the two files " }{TEXT 216 11 "qu
anser.ind" }{TEXT 232 5 " and " }{TEXT 217 11 "quanser.lib" }{TEXT 
232 98 "  into a directory of your choice, like for example: \"C:\\Pro
gram Files\\Quanser\\Maple Repository\". " }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
218 6 "To use" }{TEXT 232 5 " the " }{TEXT 219 13 "Quanser_Tools" }
{TEXT 232 94 " package in a Maple worksheet, add the path to its disk \+
location to the Maple global variable " }{TEXT 220 7 "libname" }{TEXT 
232 69 ". For example, this can be achieved by the following Maple com
mand: \n" }{TEXT 232 11 "libname := " }{TEXT 221 54 " \"C:/Program Fil
es/Quanser/Maple Repository\", libname:" }}}}{SECT 0 {PARA 3 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT 231 24 "Worksheet Initialization" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 41 "restart: interface( imaginaryunit = j ): " }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "with( LinearAlgebra ):" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 69 "libname := \"C:/Program Files/Quans
er/Maple Repository\", \".\", libname:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "with( Quanser_Tools );" }}{PARA 210 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
