" = second link end-effector angular position (relative to the first l
ink end-effector): the zero angle is defined as the starting position.
" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 36 "q := [ theta[21](t), the
ta[22](t) ];" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"qG7$-&%&thetaG6#\"
#@6#%\"tG-&%&thetaG6#\"#A6#%\"tG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 
63 "Nq = number of Lagrangian coordinates (e.g. here, it is Nq = 2)" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 41 "Nq is also the number of position state
s." }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "Nq := nops( q ):" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 101 "qd = first-order time derivative of the
 generalized coordinates, e.g. position and angular velocities" }}
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "qd := map( diff, q, t );" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#qdG7$-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#\"#@6#%\"tG%\"
tG-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#\"#A6#%\"tG%\"tG" }}}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
234 0 "" }}{SECT 0 {PARA 4 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 21 "State-Space Variables
" }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 103 "The chosen states should at least \+
include the generalized coordinates and their first-time derivatives."
 }}{PARA 15 "" 0 "" {TEXT 232 22 "X is the state vector." }}{PARA 15 "
" 0 "" {TEXT 232 141 "In the state vector X: Lagrangian coordinates ar
e first, followed by their first-time derivatives, and finally any oth
er states, as required." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 78 "Substi
tution sets for the states (to obtain time-independent state equations
)." }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 44 "subs_Xq := \{ seq( q[i] = X[i
], i=1..Nq ) \};\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 48 "subs_Xqd := \{ seq( qd[i] = X[i+
Nq], i=1..Nq ) \};" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%(subs_XqG<$/-&
%&thetaG6#\"#@6#%\"tG&%\"XG6#\"\"\"/-&%&thetaG6#\"#A6#%\"tG&%\"XG6#\"
\"#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%)subs_XqdG<$/-%%diffG6$-&%&th
etaG6#\"#@6#%\"tG%\"tG&%\"XG6#\"\"$/-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#\"#A6#%\"tG%
\"tG&%\"XG6#\"\"%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 34 "Substitutio
n set for the input(s)." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 41 "set the input
 to be the motor #2 current:" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "sub
s_U := \{ I[m2] = U[1] \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 109 "s
et the input to be the actuator driving force/torque (if not expressed
 as a function of the motor voltage): " }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 27 "#subs_U := \{ T[2] = U[1] \}:" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT
 234 66 "Nu = number of inputs; U = input (row) vector (e.g. U = [ V[m
] ] )" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 21 "Nu := nops( subs_U ):" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 65 "substitution set for the position
 states' second time derivatives" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 63 
"subs_Xqdd := \{ seq( diff( q[i], t$2 ) =  Xd[i+Nq], i=1..Nq ) \};" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%*subs_XqddG<$/-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#
\"#@6#%\"tG-%\"$G6$%\"tG\"\"#&%#XdG6#\"\"$/-%%diffG6$-&%&thetaG6#\"#A6
#%\"tG-%\"$G6$%\"tG\"\"#&%#XdG6#\"\"%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT
 234 87 "second time derivatives of the position states (written as ti
me-independent variables)." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 91 "The set of
