233 48 "Additional Insight: Inertia (or mass) Matrix: Fi" }}{PARA 0 ""
 0 "" {TEXT 234 118 "The nonlinear system of equations resulting from \+
the Lagrangian mechanics can be written in the following matrix form:"
 }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 59 "F( q ) . qdd + G( q, qd ) . qd + H( q
 ) . q = L( q, qd, u )" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 80 "F, G, and H ar
e called, respectively, the mass, damping, and stiffness matrices." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 27 "They are symmetric in form." }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT 234 101 "The inertia (a.k.a. mass) matrix, F, gives indic
ations regarding the coupling existing in the system." }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "Fi := Matrix( Nq, Nq ):" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "for i from 1 to Nq do\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 
24 "  for k from 1 to Nq do\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 72 "    Fi[ i, k ] := sim
plify( diff( op( 1, EOM_states[i] ), Xd[k+Nq] ) );\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 
63 "    Fi[ i, k ] := collect( combine( Fi[ i, k ], trig ), cos );\n" 
}{MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "  end do;\n" }{MPLTEXT 1 0 7 "end do:" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 234 30 "Here, Fi shows a linear system" }}{PARA 
